text: Ekaterina Dmitriyevna Alexandrovskaya (; 1 January 2000 â€“ 17 July 2020) was a Russian-Australian pair skater. With skating partner, Harley Windsor, she was the 2017 CS Tallinn Trophy champion, the 2017 CS Nebelhorn Trophy bronze medallist, the 2018 CS U.S. Classic bronze medallist and a two-time Australian national champion (2016 and 2018). Alexandrovskaya was born in Moscow. She became an Australian citizen in October 2017. On 17 July 2020, she killed herself in Moscow at the age of 20. ==References== Category:2000 births Category:Olympians for Australia Category:Naturalised citizens of Australia Category:Russian figure skaters Category:Sportspeople from Moscow Category:Sportspeople from Sydney Category:Sportspeople who committed suicide Category:Suicide in 2020 Category:Suicides by jumping Category:Competitors at the 2018 Winter Olympics Category:Suicides in Australia
